    "is_good_patch": false,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix missing positioning measurement report comparison function\n\n### Summary\nThe F1AP positioning functionality was missing the required `eq_positioning_measurement_report()` function that is needed for comparing PositioningMeasurementReport PDUs. This caused compilation errors when building the F1AP library with positioning support enabled.\n\nThe function was referenced in other parts of the codebase but the actual implementation was missing entirely. This manifested as undefined reference errors during linking when positioning features were enabled.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair2/F1AP/lib/f1ap_positioning.c`: Added new file containing the `eq_positioning_measurement_report()` function implementation\n- `openair2/F1AP/lib/f1ap_positioning.h`: Added new header file with function declaration\n- `openair2/F1AP/lib/CMakeLists.txt`: Added new source file to build\n- `openair2/F1AP/lib/f1ap_lib_includes.h`: Added header to common includes\n\nThe implementation provides basic NULL checking and protocolIEs list count comparison. The function returns BOOLEAN type as expected by the ASN.1 framework and follows the same naming conventions used throughout the F1AP codebase.\n"
}